casebody.data:
ELLIOTT MANUFACTURING COMPANY, a Corporation, Appellant, v. Louis B. SAMMIS and Frank R. HOOD, Appellees. No. 9039. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 5, 1938. Herbert A. Huebner, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Percy S. Webster and Roger B. Webster, both of Stockton, Cal., for appellees.

Before WILBUR, GARRECPIT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for appellees, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed for failure of appellant to file record and docket cause; that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
